# Cinema Tickets Coding Exercise

## Overview
This solution implements the `TicketService` interface for the DWP cinema ticket exercise.

## Business Rules Covered
- Supports ADULT, CHILD, and INFANT tickets
- Maximum 25 tickets per transaction
- Child and infant tickets require at least one adult
- Infants do not require a seat
- One infant per adult
- Correct payment and seat reservation logic

## Design Principles
- Clean code
- Immutable request object
- Defensive validation
- Single responsibility methods
- Unit tested

## Assumptions
- One infant per adult lap
- Zero / negative ticket quantities are invalid
- Empty requests are invalid